review_blob: 12 Oz. Bottle poured into a frosty mug. Pours like 40 weight oil with a nice thick, dark head. Smells of coffee and licorice. Nice sweet flavor that has a nice lingering aftertaste. Found this 6 pack of 12 Oz. bottles and a local market. Im going back for more.
16 Oz. Bottle poured into a pint glass. Pours very dark with a solid light brown head which has some hang time. No odor detected. Creamy coffee taste with an earthy aftertaste. Great Beer!

12 Oz. Bottle poured. Reddish brown with a nice tan head. I could smell the fruit and caramel while I poured. Nice solid taste of plum with a hint of chocolate. Nice smooth aftertaste. Great fall beer.

16 oz. bottle. I bought this beer because the store had a BeerRate.com sign on it saying it was a 90+ beer. What a lie! Pours a cloudy yellow with no head. Has a slightly fruity aroma with zero taste. This beer literally has NO TASTE!...YUCK.
12 oz Bottle. Pours like a cola with a small head. Smells earthy. Taste is slightly sweet like brown sugar and almonds. light body with a nice smooth finish. Good beer!

12 Oz. Bottle poured into a chilled glass. Slight hoppy aroma with definite chocolate background. Pours dark brown with a nice tan head. Lightly sweet taste and again, you can sense the chocolate in the background. Creamy texture with a great follow through. Love this beer!

12 oz Bottle poured into a tulip. You can smell the grapefruit immediately along with the hops. Pours a dark gold with a off-white head that dissipates rather quickly. Fruity taste with a slight bitterness. Remains on the roof of the mouth for quite a while. I have never been a fan of "Fruiting the Beer", but this works.

2013 22 oz. Bottle poured into a snifter. Fruity aroma with a nice dark mahogany pour. Not much of a head. Sweet and fruity with a very nice follow through. My first time with these Alaska brews but certainly not my last. Very nice!
beer_name: Alaskan Pilot Series: Barley Wine Ale

review_blob: 2013 From a 22 oz. Bottle. Like black coffee. Absolutely no head at all. You can immediately smell and taste the smoke. Great earthy flavor with a smooth lingering after taste. Wish I bought more than 1.

12oz Bottle poured into a pint glass. Slightly floral and smoky. Poured as a hazy red. The head dissipated in about 45 seconds. A little sour and not quite like any Oktoberfest I have had before. Very light on the palate and fortunately the taste quickly disappears. Might be ok to boil Brats in.
12 oz. Bottle poured into a pilsner glass. Great golden color with a very large head. Floral odor, light bitter taste with a very nice aftertaste.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Extra! Ale
